properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 15 at 4:51AM CST until January 15 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN
properties.description:
...SNOW ACCUMULATIONS LIKELY ACROSS CENTRAL MINNESOTA AND LIGHT
ICING LIKELY OVER FAR SOUTHERN MINNESOTA TODAY...

.Snow will continue this morning across central Minnesota. Two to
four inches of snow is expected for Douglas, Todd, Morrison,
Mille Lacs and Kanabec counties. Snow will diminish this
afternoon. In addition, freezing drizzle can be expected this
morning over far southern Minnesota, including the Interstate
90 corridor. A few hundredths of an inch of ice accretion is
expected along and south of a line from Darfur to Madelia to
Waseca to Owatonna.

Motorists should exercise caution and allow extra time when
traveling this morning. Please drive slowly and with caution if
roads are slippery.

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation. Total snow accumulations of up to
one inch and ice accumulations of a few hundredths of an inch.

* WHERE...Watonwan, Blue Earth, Waseca and Steele Counties.

* WHEN...Until noon CST today.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning commute.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Motorists should exercise caution and allow
extra time when traveling. Please drive slowly and with caution
if roads are slippery.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON CST TODAY
